## Test API Requests

### 1. Register User (POST /users/register)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/users/register \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "name": "John Doe",
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "password123",
    "role": "student"
  }'
```

### 2. Login User (POST /users/login)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/users/login \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "email": "john@example.com",
    "password": "password123"
  }'
```

### 3. Get All Courses (GET /courses)
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:4000/courses
```

### 4. Create Course (POST /courses)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/courses \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "title": "New Course",
    "description": "Course description",
    "category": "Development",
    "level": "beginner",
    "duration": 40,
    "price": 49.99,
    "instructor": "Jane Smith",
    "instructorId": "instructor-id"
  }'
```

### 5. Get Course Details (GET /courses/:courseId)
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:4000/courses/course-id-here
```

### 6. Enroll in Course (POST /enrollments/enroll)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/enrollments/enroll \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN" \
  -d '{
    "courseId": "course-id-here"
  }'
```

### 7. Get User Enrollments (GET /enrollments/my-enrollments)
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:4000/enrollments/my-enrollments \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN"
```

### 8. Track Progress (POST /progress/track)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/progress/track \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN" \
  -d '{
    "userId": "user-id",
    "courseId": "course-id",
    "lessonId": "lesson-id",
    "lessonTitle": "Lesson Title",
    "isCompleted": true
  }'
```

### 9. Get User Progress (GET /progress/my-progress)
```bash
curl -X GET http://localhost:4000/progress/my-progress \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN"
```

### 10. Generate Certificate (POST /certificates/generate)
```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:4000/certificates/generate \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN" \
  -d '{
    "userId": "user-id",
    "courseId": "course-id",
    "courseName": "Course Name",
    "studentName": "Student Name",
    "instructorName": "Instructor Name",
    "score": 95,
    "skills": ["Skill1", "Skill2"]
  }'
```

